ody.kc-css-system .kc-css-1755816{padding-right: 27px;}body.kc-css-system .kc-css-3438433{margin-top: 50px;margin-bottom: 50px;}body.kc-css-system .kc-css-1741041{text-align: right;padding-top: 35px;padding-right: 30px;}body.kc-css-system .kc-css-1317034{float: right;}body.kc-css-system .kc-css-2154886.kc_title,body.kc-css-system .kc-css-2154886 .kc_title,body.kc-css-system .kc-css-2154886 .kc_title a.kc_title_link{font-family: Roboto Slab;font-size: 30px;}body.kc-css-system .kc-css-1890232{padding-left: 27px;}@media only screen and (max-width: 999px){body.kc-css-system .kc-css-2466614{padding-left: 0px;}body.kc-css-system .kc-css-1136994{padding-right: 0px;}body.kc-css-system .kc-css-1530360{padding-left: 0px;}body.kc-css-system .kc-css-1741041{padding-right: 0px;}}@media only screen and (max-width: 767px){body.kc-css-system .kc-css-3070714{padding-top: 30px;padding-bottom: 30px;}body.kc-css-system .kc-css-2466614{padding-left: 0px;}body.kc-css-system .kc-css-1136994{padding-right: 0px;}body.kc-css-system .kc-css-1530360{padding-left: 0px;}body.kc-css-system .kc-css-1741041{padding-right: 0px;}}@media only screen and (max-width: 479px){body.kc-css-system .kc-css-3070714{padding-top: 35px;padding-bottom: 35px;}body.kc-css-system .kc-css-728880{margin-top: 30px;margin-bottom: 30px;}body.kc-css-system .kc-css-2466614{padding-left: 0px;}body.kc-css-system .kc-css-1069810{margin-top: 30px;margin-bottom: 30px;}body.kc-css-system .kc-css-1136994{padding-right: 0px;}body.kc-css-system .kc-css-2570840{padding-left: 15px;}body.kc-css-system .kc-css-2907921{margin-top: 30px;margin-bottom: 30px;}body.kc-css-system .kc-css-1530360{padding-left: 0px;}body.kc-css-system .kc-css-3438433{margin-top: 30px;margin-bottom: 30px;}body.kc-css-system .kc-css-1741041{padding-right: 0px;}body.kc-css-system .kc-css-2884689{padding-left: 15px;}}</style><section data-kc-fullwidth=\"row\" class=\"kc-elm kc-css-3070714 kc_row\"><div class=\"kc-row-container  kc-container\"><div class=\"kc-wrap-columns\"><div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-172226 kc_col-sm-12 kc_column kc_col-sm-12\"><div class=\"kc-col-container\">\r\n	<div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-1590690 \">\r\n		<div class=\"section-title text-center  \">\r\n						<h2>Flagship Programs</h2>\r\n						<div class=\"icon-img\">\r\n				<img src=\"http://dev.ata.com/wp-content/plugins/vorosa-helper-plugin/include/shortcode/images/1.png\" class=\"attachment-full size-full\" alt=\"\" />			</div>\r\n						<p>The agriculture sector features three flagship programs. These are large, multi-partnered approaches that create high levels of investment efficiency. All of the programs feature resource alignment through ministry-based coordination units and resource harmonization through several modalities, including basket-funding, parallel funding, and common work plans.</p>\r\n					</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-728880 kc_row kc_row_inner\"><div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-3415170 kc_col-sm-6 kc_column_inner kc_col-sm-6\"><div class=\"kc_wrapper kc-col-inner-container\"><div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-3816539 kc_shortcode kc_single_image\">\n\n        <img src=\"http://dev.ata.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/programs_img1.jpg\" class=\"\" alt=\"\" />    </div>\n</div></div><div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-4008771 kc_col-sm-6 kc_column_inner kc_col-sm-6\"><div class=\"kc_wrapper kc-col-inner-container\"><div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-2466614 kc_row kc_row_inner video-info video-border\"><div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-3057840 kc_col-sm-12 kc_column_inner kc_col-sm-12\"><div class=\"kc_wrapper kc-col-inner-container\">\n<div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-1818383 kc-title-wrap \">\n\n	<h3 class=\"kc_title\">Agriculture Growth Program</h3>\n</div>\n<div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-321596 kc_text_block\"><p>The second phase Agriculture Growth Program (AGP 2), from 2015-2020, amounting to 581.8 million USD, is a multifaceted investment program operational in 157 high-potential woredas. The development objective of AGP 2 is to increase agricultural productivity and commercialization of smallholder farmers with particular focus on women and youth beneficiaries.</p>\n<p>The project comprises five components.</p>\n<p>1. Agricultural public support services will increase access to public agricultural services for smallholder farmers.</p>\n<p>2. Agricultural research will increase the supply of demand-driven agricultural technologies, which directly link to the other components.</p>\n<p>3. Small-scale irrigation will increase the access to and efficient utilization of irrigation water by smallholder farmers.</p>\n<p>4. Agricultural marketing and value chains will commercialize smallholder farmers through increased access to input and output markets.</p>\n<p>5. Project management, capacity building, and M&amp;E will ensure efficient project implementation, M&amp;E of results, and a consistent and effective approach to capacity building. Nutrition, gender, and climate smart agriculture considerations are mainstreamed throughout all components.</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-1069810 kc_row kc_row_inner\"><div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-2667294 kc_col-sm-6 kc_column_inner kc_col-sm-6\"><div class=\"kc_wrapper kc-col-inner-container\"><div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-1136994 kc_row kc_row_inner video-info video-border-two\"><div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-3167769 kc_col-sm-12 kc_column_inner kc_col-sm-12\"><div class=\"kc_wrapper kc-col-inner-container\">\n<div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-484946 kc-title-wrap \">\n\n	<h3 class=\"kc_title\">Sustainable Land Management Program\r\n</h3>\n</div>\n<div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-1105487 kc_text_block\"><p>The second phase Sustainable Land Management Program (SLMP 2), covering the years 2014-2019 and 107 million USD, conducts activities to rehabilitate and protect natural resources. Its objective is to reduce land degradation and improve land productivity in selected watersheds in the highlands of Ethiopia.</p>\n<p>There are four components to the project.</p>\n<p>1. Integrated watershed and landscape management supports scale-up and adoption of appropriate sustainable land and water management technologies and practices by smallholder farmers and communities.</p>\n<p>2. Institutional strengthening, capacity development and knowledge generation and management complements on-the-ground activities to be implemented under component one by strengthening and enhancing institutional capacity and building relevant skills and knowledge of stakeholders (including government agencies, research organizations and academia involved in the sustainable natural resource management, as well as the private sector, community leaders and smallholder farmers).</p>\n<p>3. Rural land administration enhances the tenure security of smallholder farmers in order to increase their motivation to adopt sustainable land and water management practices on communal and individual land.</p>\n<p>4. Enhancing the skills and capacities of project managers and administrators.</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-2570840 kc_col-sm-6 kc_column_inner kc_col-sm-6\"><div class=\"kc_wrapper kc-col-inner-container\"><div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-2120132 kc_shortcode kc_single_image\">\n\n        <img src=\"http://dev.ata.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/programs_img2.jpg\" class=\"\" alt=\"\" />    </div>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-2907921 kc_row kc_row_inner\"><div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-2584205 kc_col-sm-6 kc_column_inner kc_col-sm-6\"><div class=\"kc_wrapper kc-col-inner-container\"><div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-3648565 kc_shortcode kc_single_image\">\n\n        <img src=\"http://dev.ata.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/programs_img3.jpg\" class=\"\" alt=\"\" />    </div>\n</div></div><div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-1438223 kc_col-sm-6 kc_column_inner kc_col-sm-6\"><div class=\"kc_wrapper kc-col-inner-container\"><div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-1530360 kc_row kc_row_inner video-info video-border\"><div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-44614 kc_col-sm-12 kc_column_inner kc_col-sm-12\"><div class=\"kc_wrapper kc-col-inner-container\">\n<div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-3405847 kc-title-wrap \">\n\n	<h3 class=\"kc_title\">Productive Safety Net Program</h3>\n</div>\n<div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-1755816 kc_text_block\"><p>The fourth phase Productive Safety Net Program (PSNP 4), spanning from 2015 to 2020, with an investment of 4.8 billion USD, ensures food security through a system of food/cash transfers to vulnerable households. PSNP 4 has the objective to increase access to safety net and disaster risk management systems, complementary livelihoods services, and nutrition support for food insecure households in rural Ethiopia. Three components will contribute to the achievement of the PSNP objective.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Component one</strong> will provide support to the social protection and disaster risk management systems, including targeting, registration capacity development, management information systems, early warning triggers, and response mechanisms.</li>\n<li><strong>Component two</strong> will be delivered through three sub-components delivering key services of:\n<ul>\n<li>Safety net transfers to chronically food insecure households and support to a scalable response mechanism for transitory needs;</li>\n<li>Sustainable community assets and human capital investments and;</li>\n<li>Enhanced access to complementary livelihoods services for client households through crop and livestock production, off-farm income generating services, and labor/employment linkages.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Component three will support sustainable capacity development and institutional strengthening to support the PSNP.</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-3438433 kc_row kc_row_inner\"><div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-3446420 kc_col-sm-6 kc_column_inner kc_col-sm-6\"><div class=\"kc_wrapper kc-col-inner-container\"><div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-1741041 kc_row kc_row_inner video-info video-border-two\"><div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-1317034 kc_col-sm-12 kc_column_inner kc_col-sm-12\"><div class=\"kc_wrapper kc-col-inner-container\">\n<div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-2154886 kc-title-wrap \">\n\n	<h3 class=\"kc_title\">National Agriculture Investment Plan\r\n\r\n</h3>\n</div>\n<div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-1890232 kc_text_block\"><p>Ethiopia’s broad development goals are described in the Growth and Transformation Plan 2 (GTP2) (2015-2020), while agriculture sector goals are defined specifically in the National Agricultural Investment Framework (NAIF), which is currently being developed. The NAIF will operationalize the agricultural GTP 2, provide a framework for investment in the agriculture sector, and represent Ethiopia’s second generation Comprehensive Africa Agriculture Development Plan (CAADP) investment plan.</p>\n</div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-2884689 kc_col-sm-6 kc_column_inner kc_col-sm-6\"><div class=\"kc_wrapper kc-col-inner-container\"><div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-2860732 kc_shortcode kc_single_image\">\n\n        <img src=\"http://dev.ata.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/programs_img4.jpg\" class=\"\" alt=\"\" />    </div>\n</div></div></div></div></div></div></div></section>', 'Programs', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'programs-2', '', '', '2018-06-05 22:04:04', '2018-06-05 22:04:04', '[kc_row _id=\"427115\" cols_gap=\"{`kc-css`:{}}\" use_container=\"yes\" force=\"yes\" css_custom=\"{`kc-css`:{`479`:{`box`:{`padding|`:`35px inherit 35px inherit`}},`767`:{`box`:{`padding|`:`30px inherit 30px inherit`}},`any`:{`background`:{`background|`:`eyJjb2xvciI6IiNmOGY4ZjgiLCJsaW5lYXJHcmFkaWVudCI6WyIiXSwiaW1hZ2UiOiJub25lIiwicG9zaXRpb24iOiIwJSAwJSIsInNpemUiOiJhdXRvIiwicmVwZWF0IjoicmVwZWF0IiwiYXR0YWNobWVudCI6InNjcm9sbCIsImFkdmFuY2VkIjowfQ==`},`box`:{`padding|`:`70px inherit 70px inherit`}}}}\"][kc_column width=\"12/12\" _id=\"138705\"][vorosa_section_title title=\"RmxhZ3NoaXAgUHJvZ3JhbXM=\" description=\"\" sec_title_box_icon=\"http://dev.ata.com/wp-content/plugins/vorosa-helper-plugin/include/shortcode/images/1.png\" _id=\"910444\" sec_title_icon_size=\"full\"][kc_row_inner _id=\"845185\" cols_gap=\"{`kc-css`:{}}\" css_custom=\"{`kc-css`:{`479`:{`box`:{`margin|`:`30px inherit 30px inherit`}},`any`:{`box`:{`margin|`:`50px inherit 50px inherit`}}}}\"][kc_column_inner width=\"50%\" _id=\"863034\" css_custom=\"{`kc-css`:{}}\"][kc_single_image image_size=\"full\" _id=\"604637\" image_source=\"media_library\" image=\"1716\"][/kc_column_inner][kc_column_inner width=\"50%\" _id=\"687066\"][kc_row_inner# _id=\"764442\" cols_gap=\"{`kc-css`:{}}\" row_class=\"video-info video-border\" css_custom=\"{`kc-css`:{`479`:{`box`:{`padding|`:`inherit inherit inherit 0px`}},`767`:{`box`:{`padding|`:`inherit inherit inherit 0px`}},`999`:{`box`:{`padding|`:`inherit inherit inherit 0px`}},`any`:{`box`:{`padding|`:`35px inherit inherit 30px`}}}}\"][kc_column_inner# width=\"100%\" _id=\"481005\" css_custom=\"{`kc-css`:{}}\"][kc_title text=\"QWdyaWN1bHR1cmUgR3Jvd3RoIFByb2dyYW0=\" _id=\"488103\" type=\"h3\" css_custom=\"{`kc-css`:{`any`:{`title-style`:{`font-family|+.kc_title,.kc_title,.kc_title a.kc_title_link`:`Roboto Slab`,`font-size|+.kc_title,.kc_title,.kc_title a.kc_title_link`:`30px`}}}}\"][kc_column_text _id=\"639878\" css_custom=\"{`kc-css`:{`any`:{`box`:{`padding|`:`inherit 27px inherit inherit`}}}}\"]\r\n\r\nThe second phase Agriculture Growth Program (AGP 2), from 2015-2020, amounting to 581.8 million USD, is a multifaceted investment program operational in 157 high-potential woredas. The development objective of AGP 2 is to increase agricultural productivity and commercialization of smallholder farmers with particular focus on women and youth beneficiaries.\r\n\r\nThe project comprises five components.\r\n\r\n1. Agricultural public support services will increase access to public agricultural services for smallholder farmers.\r\n\r\n2. Agricultural research will increase the supply of demand-driven agricultural technologies, which directly link to the other components.\r\n\r\n3. Small-scale irrigation will increase the access to and efficient utilization of irrigation water by smallholder farmers.\r\n\r\n4. Agricultural marketing and value chains will commercialize smallholder farmers through increased access to input and output markets.\r\n\r\n5. Project management, capacity building, and M&amp;E will ensure efficient project implementation, M&amp;E of results, and a consistent and effective approach to capacity building. Nutrition, gender, and climate smart agriculture considerations are mainstreamed throughout all components.\r\n\r\n[/kc_column_text][/kc_column_inner#][/kc_row_inner#][/kc_column_inner][/kc_row_inner][kc_row_inner _id=\"189672\" cols_gap=\"{`kc-css`:{}}\" css_custom=\"{`kc-css`:{`479`:{`box`:{`margin|`:`30px inherit 30px inherit`}},`any`:{`box`:{`margin|`:`50px inherit 50px inherit`}}}}\"][kc_column_inner width=\"50%\" _id=\"909492\"][kc_row_inner# _id=\"517080\" cols_gap=\"{`kc-css`:{}}\" css_custom=\"{`kc-css`:{`479`:{`box`:{`padding|`:`inherit 0px inherit inherit`}},`767`:{`box`:{`padding|`:`inherit 0px inherit inherit`}},`999`:{`box`:{`padding|`:`inherit 0px inherit inherit`}},`any`:{`typography`:{`text-align|`:`right`},`box`:{`padding|`:`35px 30px inherit inherit`}}}}\" row_class=\"video-info video-border-two\"][kc_column_inner# width=\"100%\" _id=\"385225\" css_custom=\"{`kc-css`:{`any`:{`box`:{`float|`:`right`}}}}\"][kc_title text=\"U3VzdGFpbmFibGUgTGFuZCBNYW5hZ2VtZW50IFByb2dyYW0NCg==\" _id=\"661832\" type=\"h3\" css_custom=\"{`kc-css`:{`any`:{`title-style`:{`font-family|+.kc_title,.kc_title,.kc_title a.kc_title_link`:`Roboto Slab`,`font-size|+.kc_title,.kc_title,.kc_title a.kc_title_link`:`30px`}}}}\"][kc_column_text _id=\"263582\" css_custom=\"{`kc-css`:{`any`:{`box`:{`padding|`:`inherit inherit inherit 27px`}}}}\"]\r\n\r\nThe second phase Sustainable Land Management Program (SLMP 2), covering the years 2014-2019 and 107 million USD, conducts activities to rehabilitate and protect natural resources. Its objective is to reduce land degradation and improve land productivity in selected watersheds in the highlands of Ethiopia.\r\n\r\nThere are four components to the project.\r\n\r\n1. Integrated watershed and landscape management supports scale-up and adoption of appropriate sustainable land and water management technologies and practices by smallholder farmers and communities.\r\n\r\n2. Institutional strengthening, capacity development and knowledge generation and management complements on-the-ground activities to be implemented under component one by strengthening and enhancing institutional capacity and building relevant skills and knowledge of stakeholders (including government agencies, research organizations and academia involved in the sustainable natural resource management, as well as the private sector, community leaders and smallholder farmers).\r\n\r\n3. Rural land administration enhances the tenure security of smallholder farmers in order to increase their motivation to adopt sustainable land and water management practices on communal and individual land.\r\n\r\n4. Enhancing the skills and capacities of project managers and administrators.\r\n\r\n[/kc_column_text][/kc_column_inner#][/kc_row_inner#][/kc_column_inner][kc_column_inner width=\"50%\" _id=\"725967\" css_custom=\"{`kc-css`:{`479`:{`box`:{`padding|`:`inherit inherit inherit 15px`}}}}\"][kc_single_image image_size=\"full\" _id=\"355048\" image_source=\"media_library\" image=\"1718\"][/kc_column_inner][/kc_row_inner][kc_row_inner _id=\"764461\" cols_gap=\"{`kc-css`:{}}\" css_custom=\"{`kc-css`:{`479`:{`box`:{`margin|`:`30px inherit 30px inherit`}},`any`:{`box`:{`margin|`:`50px inherit 50px inherit`}}}}\"][kc_column_inner width=\"50%\" _id=\"824606\" css_custom=\"{`kc-css`:{}}\"][kc_single_image image_size=\"full\" _id=\"532083\" image_source=\"media_library\" image=\"1721\"][/kc_column_inner][kc_column_inner width=\"50%\" _id=\"273181\"][kc_row_in