`:{`any`:{`box`:{`float|`:`right`}}}}\"][kc_title text=\"TmF0aW9uYWwgQWdyaWN1bHR1cmUgSW52ZXN0bWVudCBQbGFuDQoNCg==\" _id=\"210262\" type=\"h3\" css_custom=\"{`kc-css`:{`any`:{`title-style`:{`font-family|+.kc_title,.kc_title,.kc_title a.kc_title_link`:`Roboto Slab`,`font-size|+.kc_title,.kc_title,.kc_title a.kc_title_link`:`30px`}}}}\"][kc_column_text _id=\"911838\" css_custom=\"{`kc-css`:{`any`:{`box`:{`padding|`:`inherit inherit inherit 27px`}}}}\"]\r\n\r\nEthiopia’s broad development goals are described in the Growth and Transformation Plan 2 (GTP2) (2015-2020), while agriculture sector goals are defined specifically in the National Agricultural Investment Framework (NAIF), which is currently being developed. The NAIF will operationalize the agricultural GTP 2, provide a framework for investment in the agriculture sector, and represent Ethiopia’s second generation Comprehensive Africa Agriculture Development Plan (CAADP) investment plan.\r\n\r\n[/kc_column_text][/kc_column_inner#][/kc_row_inner#][/kc_column_inner][kc_column_inner width=\"50%\" _id=\"276425\" css_custom=\"{`kc-css`:{`479`:{`box`:{`padding|`:`inherit inherit inherit 15px`}}}}\"][vorosa_video_popup video_popup_random_key=\"57461\" source=\"youtube\" video_link=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6tfFRD0enV0\" video_box_bg=\"134\" _id=\"889601\" img_size=\"full\" video_box_icon=\"111\" icon_size=\"full\"][kc_single_image image_size=\"full\" _id=\"2104\" image_source=\"media_library\" image=\"1722\"][/kc_column_inner][/kc_row_inner][/kc_column][/kc_row]', 'Programs', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1711-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-06-05 19:50:43', '2018-06-05 19:50:43', '', 1711, 'http://dev.ata.com/1711-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
